Do you love repeating outfits too?? 

Repeating outfits is one of my favourite things to do. 

If I love something, I can’t stop wearing them, and I won’t stop wearing them again and again. And this skirt is one of them. So, styled this skirt with a black shirt which I have never worn before. And tried to make it work today!

Shirt @marksandspencerindia 
Skirt @newme.asia

Would you try this? 

I have always loved styling my dresses as tops — with trousers, skirts, even jeans! But if you’re thinking of trying it and don’t want to take a big risk, start by pairing your dress with a flowy, flared skirt. It blends in nicely and also doesn’t look awkward.

And if you’ve never tried this hack… you’re seriously missing out🙆🏻‍♀️

Do you like watching these kutty vlogs? 

A few weeks ago, when my mom was visiting me in Bangalore for my birthday, it was raining every single day. But one day, we just decided to step out — rain or no rain.
Surprisingly, that day it didn’t rain at all! So my sister, mom, and I went to Commercial Street… mainly for the vibe. But let’s be honest, how can anyone go to Commercial Street and not shop? 😅
We ended up picking some tiny, cute accessories, handbags, footwear — you know, the usual Commercial Street finds!

And like always, we made a quick pitstop at Shree Saravana Bhavan for a hot cup of tea and some chats. Later, Ajay joined us and we wrapped up the day with a super comforting dinner at Hotel Empire — ghee rice, dal tadka, and paneer tikka! 

Wearing @thetrampoline.in

Read caption✨ 

Sharing something I’ve never really said out loud.

I’ve always been the kind of person who just can’t fight back.
Even when someone is rude or unkind, I freeze. I stay quiet. I walk away.
Not because I’m weak.
Not because I don’t know how to respond.

But because shouting back isn’t who I am.
And for the longest time, I felt that maybe something was wrong with me…
People around me would say,
“You’re too soft.”
“You don’t stand up for yourself.”
“You let people walk over you.”

But the truth is, this is my power.
I don’t react just because someone else is loud.
I don’t let people control how I feel.

Yes, it hurts sometimes.
But I’ve learned—just because something hurts…
doesn’t mean I have to turn it into anger.

Staying calm when the world expects you to explode…
That’s strength too.
A quiet kind of strength that no one claps for—but it’s there.

And maybe this won’t make sense to everyone.
But to the ones who feel this too—
You’re not weak. You’re just built differently. And that’s actually… a beautiful thing. 🤍

#realtalk #GRWM #softnotweak #sayitoutloud #personal #wishlinked

Good things start happening when you start seeing good around you✨

I’ve noticed this with myself…
When I’m going through a tough time, my mind just focuses on all the bad stuff. People’s flaws feel louder. Everything feels a bit heavy. I can’t really see the good, even if it’s there.

But when I try, even just a little, to look for the good things—that’s when things begin to change.
Not right away, but slowly, I start feeling stronger.

That’s when life starts to feel beautiful again. That’s when you start to see how kind and lovely people actually are.

Everyone has both—a good side and a not-so-perfect side. But when you’re able to notice just the good in people ( it’s not that easy but when you do it)—that feeling is something special. It feels calm and right.

And it’s not just about good things coming your way

The right people also come into your life when you’re ready to see the good in others.

Have you felt this too?
